						</code>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
							Example: 16 drives in 2 groups of 8 = 2 × 6 × 12TB = 144TB usable (75% efficiency)
						</p>

						<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Pros</h3>
						<ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li>Maximum redundancy (two drive failures per group)</li>
							<li>Excellent for very large drives and massive arrays</li>
							<li>Better performance than single RAID 6</li>
							<li>Can survive multiple drive failures across groups</li>
							<li>Safer rebuild than RAID 50</li>
						</ul>

						<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Cons</h3>
						<ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li>Very complex to set up and manage</li>
							<li>Expensive (requires minimum 8 drives)</li>
							<li>Lower capacity efficiency than RAID 50</li>
							<li>Write performance penalty from dual parity</li>
						</ul>

						<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Best Use Cases</h3>
